From 32fe59aea9fc547ca71c73721b44e22bb4b9523c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Message-ID: <cover.1780501030.git.rebase@local>
From: Natalie Vock <natalie.vock@gmx.de>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 08:34:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 0/3] drm/amdgpu: Explicit sync for PRT unmaps (v6.18.34 + vega-ms178 rebase)

This is the patchwork series 167515 ("drm/amdgpu: Explicit sync for PRT
unmaps") by Natalie Vock, rebased from amd-staging-drm-next onto
Linux 6.18.34 with the local "vega-ms178" customisations applied on top.

Upstream link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/series/167515/

Effect
======
Whenever PRT mappings are unmapped, the existing code implicitly syncs
to *all* in-VM submissions, stalling rendering noticeably in games that
exercise sparse residency heavily (DOOM Eternal, Resident Evil 4 RT,
Forza Horizon 5, etc.).  This series adds AMDGPU_VM_EXPLICIT_SYNC, a
new VM-op flag that lets Mesa request explicit synchronisation for the
unmap path.  The kernel safety net only honours the flag when *every*
freed mapping is either always-valid (already covered by dma-resv) or
PRT (no real backing memory); otherwise the operation is silently
downgraded to the prior implicit-sync semantics, so a malicious or
buggy userspace cannot cause use-after-free of GPU-visible memory.

Series structure
================
  [1/3] drm/amdgpu: Add and use vm_update_ctx struct
        - Introduces struct amdgpu_vm_update_ctx and threads it through
          all VM-map/unmap entry points; per-operation freed list lets
          callers reason about a single VM update in isolation.
  [2/3] drm/amdgpu: Implement explicit sync for PRT unmaps
        - Adds AMDGPU_VM_EXPLICIT_SYNC UAPI flag (bit 10), hooks it up
          in amdgpu_gem_va_ioctl, and downgrades the sync mode in
          amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_ensure_unmap_synced when (and only when)
          every freed mapping qualifies.
  [3/3] drm/amdgpu: Bump minor version (3.64 -> 3.65)

Rebase deltas vs amd-staging-drm-next
=====================================
The series was authored against amd-staging-drm-next in March 2026 and
does not apply cleanly to v6.18.34.  Adjustments:

  * mes_v12_1.c does not exist in v6.18.34 (it only contains the
    mes_v12_1_map_test_bo self-test).  The corresponding hunk has been
    dropped; functional behaviour is unaffected.
  * The userq gem_va_unmap path (bo_va->userq_va_mapped /
    amdgpu_userq_gem_va_unmap_validate) does not exist in v6.18.34.
    The one-line caller-signature hunk in amdgpu_userq.c was dropped.
  * Logging style preserved as DRM_ERROR(...) (v6.18.34) rather than
    drm_err(adev_to_drm(adev), ...) used in staging-next.
  * Comment in amdgpu_userq_bo_validate kept as "moves the bo_va to the
    done list" (v6.18.34 wording) rather than the staging-next "idle".

Adjustments for the local vega-ms178 patch
==========================================
  * amdgpu_gem_va_ioctl: vega keeps its two-label cleanup (error:
    plus error_put_gobj:) and the AMDGPU_GEM_SYNCOBJ_STACK_SIZE
    optimisations for amdgpu_gem_add_input_fence.  An explicit
    amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_fini(&update_ctx) was added before the
    goto error_put_gobj after add_input_fence failure to plug the
    leak window introduced by the upstream patch's single-label
    design.
  * amdgpu_gem_object_open: vega's eviction-fence-attach failure
    cleanup calls amdgpu_vm_bo_del(); a stack-local update_ctx is
    created and finalised around it so the new signature is satisfied
    without restructuring vega's logic.
  * amdgpu_gem_object_close: rearranged so amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_init
    runs unconditionally before any goto out_unlock, and the matching
    fini is reached on every exit path.  This fixes upstream bug #2
    (see below) for this caller.
  * Vega's prefault helpers and Raptor Lake tuning constants were
    left untouched; they do not interact with the VM-update path.

Upstream bugs fixed in this rebase
==================================
Two issues in the original patch that I am highly confident are real:

  1. amdgpu_vm_handle_moved
     Replaced "return r" with "goto error" in the success path but
     left "return 0" at the end of the function, so any successful
     handle_moved call would return the (uninitialised on success) r.
     Fixed by inserting an explicit "r = 0;" before the error: label.
     Worth reporting upstream regardless of v6.18.34.

  2. amdgpu_gem_object_close
     The upstream patch adds amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_init() but no
     matching _fini().  That leaks all amdgpu_sync hashtable entries
     plus any freed mappings recorded during amdgpu_vm_bo_del() /
     amdgpu_vm_clear_freed() for every BO closed by a process.
     Fixed by restructuring so init() runs unconditionally before
     drm_exec_init() and fini() runs on every out_unlock path.

Audit scope
===========
- All 20 amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_init / 22 amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_fini
  call sites traced; every error path verified to call fini, every
  early return verified to occur before init.
- All 7 modified function signatures verified in every caller in
  the amdgpu tree (zero stale (adev, ...) calls).
- Brace and goto-label balance verified on every modified file.
- Lock discipline of the new list_splice into vm->delayed_freed in
  amdgpu_vm_update_ctx_fini verified against every caller (VM PD
  reservation lock held in all cases).
- AMDGPU_VM_EXPLICIT_SYNC (1 << 10) verified unused in v6.18.34's
  AMDGPU_VM_* flag space; added to both valid_flags and prt_flags.
- explicit_sync_unmap bool: precedence check on
    ctx->explicit_sync_unmap &= a || (b & FLAG)
  confirmed parses as &= (a || (b & FLAG)) per C precedence.
- bo_va NULL-safety verified at every add_freed_mapping call site
  (clear_mappings derives it from the interval-tree iterator;
  bo_unmap / bo_del receive it as a function parameter).

Apply order
===========
Apply against a v6.18.34 tree with the local kernel-raptorlake-experiments
stack already installed, i.e. after 0001-vega-ms178.patch:

    patch -Np1 < 0001-drm-amdgpu-Add-and-use-vm_update_ctx-struct.patch
    patch -Np1 < 0002-drm-amdgpu-Implement-explicit-sync-for-PRT-unmaps.patch
    patch -Np1 < 0003-drm-amdgpu-Bump-minor-version.patch

Or, equivalently, with git:

    git am 0001-*.patch 0002-*.patch 0003-*.patch

Verified to apply cleanly (zero rejects) against v6.18.34 + the cs/gem/kms
subset of 0001-vega-ms178.patch.

